<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,266,2093]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,487,1741,1768]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—This species is endemic to the Brazilian Central Planalto, in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[1314,1382,1742,1768]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[272,499,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[515,786,1778,1804]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark 2002</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record for the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1237,1290,1778,1804]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Pará</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londono" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Trinius" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Eremocaulon capitatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in gallery forests and mata ciliar in sandy soils, at 300 to 900 meters (
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[1135,1408,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark 2002</bibRefCitation>
). In Serra do Cachimbo, this species was found in riparian forests of 
<emphasis box="[870,979,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Cerradão</emphasis>
and Open ombrophilous forest, along the margins of the Braço Norte (CPBV) and Curuá (REBIONSC) rivers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,266,2093]" lastBlockId="11.[136,1452,158,1121]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1921,1947]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londono" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Trinius" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[356,625,1922,1948]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatum">
<emphasis box="[356,625,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Eremocaulon capitatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from its congeners by the culms 
<quantity box="[1183,1254,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" unit="m" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8 m</quantity>
tall, the presence of infra- and supranodal bands of white trichomes, culm leaf sheaths abaxially glabrescent, margins densely ciliate, and midnerve of the foliage leaves strongly excentric. In the Serra do Cachimbo, it differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Munro (1868: 85)" authorityName="Munro" authorityPageNumber="85" authorityYear="1868" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Guadua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis box="[1152,1369,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Guadua paniculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Munro, C." pageId="10" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 158" refId="ref25666" refString="Munro, C. (1868) A monograph of Bambusaceae, including descriptions of all the species. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 26 (1): 1 - 158." type="journal article" year="1868">Munro (1868: 85)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which also has infra- and supranodal bands of white trichomes on the culms, by the branch complement without thorns (vs. bearing thorns), persistent culm leaves, with blades reflexed, ovate-lanceolate (vs. caducous culm leaves, blades erect, triangular) and synflorescences composed of 6 capitate coflorescences, pseudospikelets 12–13 × 
<quantity box="[162,279,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="2.4" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.8">1.8–3 mm</quantity>
and palea with enfolding margins glabrous except apically puberulous and waxy (vs. 4–8 paniculate coflorescences, pseudospikelets ca. 26 × 
<quantity box="[596,661,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
and palea margins glabrous).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,1121]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">
The basionym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londono" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Trinius" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[392,663,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatum">
<emphasis box="[392,663,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Eremocaulon capitatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Trinius (1835: 626)" authorityName="Trinius" authorityPageNumber="626" authorityYear="1835" box="[679,1118,266,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[679,885,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Bambusa capitata</emphasis>
Trinius (1835: 626)
</taxonomicName>
, was described based on 
<specimenCount pageId="11" pageNumber="110" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[388,456,302,328]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by Ludwig Riedel, which contains the annotation “in ripa flum. Pardo Bras.”. The C.B. Trinius Gramineae Herbarium at LE possesses three sheets in the folder labeled “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trinius" authorityYear="1835" box="[1095,1302,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[1095,1302,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Bambusa capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”: LE-TRIN-3212.01, LE-TRIN-3211.01, and LE-TRIN-3211.02 (Soreng 
<emphasis box="[851,913,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">et al.</emphasis>
1994). The specimen LE-TRIN-3212.01 is a duplicate of the C.L. Willdenow herbarium (B-W-07013-01 0), with the annotations “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; Kunth (1830: 325)" authorityName="Kunth" authorityPageNumber="325" authorityYear="1830" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nastus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatus">
<emphasis box="[1093,1294,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Nastus capitatus”</emphasis>
Kunth (1830: 325)
</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trinius" authorityYear="1835" box="[258,383,447,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[258,383,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">B. capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” [which can be 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kunth 1830: 325) Willdenow ex Ruprecht (1840: 133)" authorityName="Ruprecht" authorityPageNumber="133" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" baseAuthorityPageNumber="325" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[573,1419,446,473]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[573,778,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Bambusa capitata</emphasis>
(Kunth 1830: 325) Willdenow ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruprecht, F. J. I." box="[1175,1419,446,472]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" pagination="91 - 166" refId="ref26316" refString="Ruprecht, F. J. I. (1840) Bambuseas. Memoires de l'Academie imperiale des sciences de St. - Petersbourg. 6 e serie. Sciences mathematiques, Seconde partie. Sciences naturelles 5 (2): 91 - 166." type="journal article" year="1840">Ruprecht (1840: 133)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kunth 1830: 325) Munro (1868: 145)" authorityName="Munro" authorityPageNumber="145" authorityYear="1868" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" baseAuthorityPageNumber="325" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[136,771,482,509]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Beesha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[136,318,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Beesha capitata</emphasis>
(Kunth 1830: 325) 
<bibRefCitation author="Munro, C." box="[548,771,482,509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 158" refId="ref25666" refString="Munro, C. (1868) A monograph of Bambusaceae, including descriptions of all the species. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 26 (1): 1 - 158." type="journal article" year="1868">Munro (1868: 145)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
], both synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kunth 1830: 325) Soetjami Dransfield (1998: 391)" authorityName="Soetjami Dransfield" authorityPageNumber="391" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" baseAuthorityPageNumber="325" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cathariostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[1006,1290,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Cathariostachys capitata</emphasis>
(Kunth 1830: 325) Soetjami Dransfield (1998: 391)
</taxonomicName>
, a woody bamboo endemic of 
<collectingCountry box="[921,1056,518,544]" name="Madagascar" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(Dransfield 1998). The specimens LE-TRIN-3211.01 and LE-TRIN-3211.02 are 
<typeStatus box="[657,755,555,581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">syntypes</typeStatus>
and clearly fit the morphology described in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="Trinius (1835: 626)" authorityName="Trinius" authorityPageNumber="626" authorityYear="1835" box="[136,571,590,617]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[136,340,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Bambusa capitata</emphasis>
Trinius (1835: 626)
</taxonomicName>
, but only the latter has the indication of the type-locality “in ripa flum. Pardo Bras.”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,1121]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[189,470,662,688]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark (2002)</bibRefCitation>
indicated 
<emphasis box="[586,703,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Riedel s.n.</emphasis>
(LE) as the 
<typeStatus box="[842,940,662,688]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Trinius (1835: 626)" authorityName="Trinius" authorityPageNumber="626" authorityYear="1835" box="[977,1404,662,689]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[977,1180,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Bambusa capitata</emphasis>
Trinius (1835: 626)
</taxonomicName>
and considered 
<emphasis box="[268,392,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Riedel 430</emphasis>
(G-00099474, K-000433088, NY-00862741, and US-00026623-fragm. ex LE) as “possible isotypes”. The status of 
<typeStatus box="[407,505,734,760]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">holotype</typeStatus>
indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[657,939,734,760]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark (2002)</bibRefCitation>
is not accurate since there are 
<specimenCount box="[1285,1452,734,761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
(
<typeStatus box="[144,245,770,796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">syntypes</typeStatus>
) of 
<emphasis box="[288,404,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Riedel s.n.</emphasis>
at LE (LE-TRIN-3211.01 and LE-TRIN-3211.02). Thus, that indication can not be considered a lectotypification according to Art. 7.11 and Art. 9.23 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[946,1180,806,832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" refId="ref27125" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[1047,1108,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, among the specimens referred to as possible isotypes by 
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[658,945,842,868]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, only US-00026623, a fragment from LE, is indeed part of the type collection. The specimens labeled 
<emphasis box="[784,905,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Riedel 430</emphasis>
(G-00099474, K-000433088, NY-00862741) do not show any evidence that they belong to the type collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,1121]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">
Thus, we conclude that 
<emphasis box="[468,589,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Riedel s.n.</emphasis>
is represented by five sheets (LE-TRIN-3211.01, LE-TRIN-3211.02, MO-2875457, P-00633835, and US-00026623), and designate the specimen LE-TRIN-3211.02 as the 
<typeStatus box="[1210,1313,986,1012]" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Trinius (1835: 626)" authorityName="Trinius" authorityPageNumber="626" authorityYear="1835" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="110">Bambusa capitata</emphasis>
Trinius (1835: 626)
</taxonomicName>
because it better fits the protologue. Besides including the exact information of the type locality “in ripa flum. Pardo Bras.”, it is deposited in the principal collection of Ludwig Riedel (Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
